      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry for the late reply,\n\nI don\u0027t intend to make this type backward compatible to `sdbusplus::message::object_path` since that one has a bunch of problems like\n\n- wrong default construction\n- bugs with `/\u003d` operator creating invalid object path\n- maybe-contains-object-path design\n\nMy initial idea for this type was that we need a type to put into generated headers / reactors to use for constexpr namespace paths,\n\nwhich could then decay to a runtime type like `sdbusplus::message::object_path` if operators like `/` are used.\n\n\nThat would then allow for safer object path construction\nin cases like\n\n```\ninline std::string getDbusReportPath(std::string_view id)\n{\n    sdbusplus::message::object_path reportsPath(\n        \"/xyz/openbmc_project/Telemetry/Reports/TelemetryService\");\n    return {reportsPath / id};\n}\n```\n\nwhere the object path invariant could be checked at compile time.\n\nSince there is still repos which do not even use `sdbusplus::message::object_path` and the problem with public `str` member could possibly be fixed, i am not prioritizing this change very much, since our existing type still has possible improvements.\n\nFor example i would hope to get the type alias `sdbusplus::object_path` merged.",
